  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Since the MRS includes the dedicated Galactic nebulae survey (Wu et al, 2021 (Wu et al,, 2022a)), the contamination of the stellar Hα fluxes by the H II regions should be considered.",
    "In this work, we identify the MRS spectra contaminated by the H II regions through the N II spectral lines on the two sides of the Hα line.",
    "The N II lines are characteristic lines of H II regions (Peimbert et al 2017; Pérez-Montero 2017) and very weak for solarlike stars.",
    "The vacuum wavelengths of the two N II lines are 6549.86 Å and 6585.27 Å, respectively (Stoughton et al, 2002), which are covered by the red band of MRS (see example MRS spectrum of the N II lines from H II regions in Appendix B).",
    "We calculate the mean fluxes in the central bands of the N II lines, and then normalize the central fluxes by the nearby continuum fluxes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Since the MRS includes the dedicated Galactic nebulae survey (Wu et al, 2021 (Wu et al,, 2022a)), the contamination of the stellar Hα fluxes by the H II regions should be considered.",
    "The N II lines are characteristic lines of H II regions (Peimbert et al 2017; Pérez-Montero 2017) and very weak for solarlike stars.",
    "The vacuum wavelengths of the two N II lines are 6549.86 Å and 6585.27 Å, respectively (Stoughton et al, 2002), which are covered by the red band of MRS (see example MRS spectrum of the N II lines from H II regions in Appendix B)."
